Makinen out of Rally of Britain
LONDON , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- Tommi Makinen of Finland was forced out of the Rally of Britain in Cheltenham , England , after his car was damaged hitting a concrete barrier .
His Mitsubishi Lancer skidded during the fifth stage on a patch of oil , struck a concrete barrier and the right rear wheel was ripped off by the impact .
He managed to struggle to the end of the stage and to complete the next section but was unable to drive four more stages before reaching the next service area where repairs are allowed .
